Here are the packed versions of some Edge extensions.
Actually, there is AdBlockPlus only.
The *.crx and *.zip versions are not yet supported by WebView4Delphi. They will crash on loading.
You have to uncompress the *.zip version into a folder respecting the folder structure contained within the ZIP file.
Then, this folder can be placed anywhere, such as C:\, for instance. So, you might get:
  C:\EdgeExtensions\AdBlockPlus
Here is a link to the contents of the AdBlockPlus.zip file:
  http:%%klaus.infinityfree.me/AdBlockPlus.zip  (replace %% by // !)
This is required because these files are way to big to fit the Github's upload restrictions.

Next, you have to launch the MessagesWithWebView4Delphi demo program.
If the MessagesWithWebView4Delphi.ini file is missing, the program will start as usual, without any extension.
Nouw, you can use the "Extension" button to open a extension configurator windows.
There, you can navigate to the AdBlockPlus folder. Select it bot do NOT open it !
Use the "Add" button to add it into the above list, than the "Validate" button to create the ini file.

After restarting the program, the presence of the ini file will be detected, and the program asks if the extensions should be loaded.
On validating this request, please wait a moment - loading an extension is SLOW !
But the home page will appear. From now on, AdBlockPlus does its work.
